Git is a free and open-source control system.
Version control is the way we as programmers track changes to our codes.
Terms
Directory: Also known as a folder on a pc.
Terminal or Command Line: interface for text command typing.
CLI: command Line Interface
CD: change directory
Code Editor: Word processor for writing code.
Repository: project or the folder/place where your project is kept.
Git: tool that tracks the changes to your codes overtime.
Github: A website that hosts your repositories.

Git Commands
Clone: To bring a repository that is hosted somewhere like github into a folder on your device.
Add: track your files and changes in git.
Commit: save your files in git.
Push: upload git commits to a remote repository like github.
Pull: download changes from remote repository to your local machine. It is the opposite of push.
